<task id="R2-015" project="SprkChat Platform Enhancement R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>PlaybookDispatcher Service — Two-Stage Intent Matching (Vector Search + LLM Refinement)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, search</tags>
    <estimated-effort>large</estimated-effort>
    <parallel-group>B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>BFF API code implementation — creates the core PlaybookDispatcher service with two-stage AI matching; central component for FR-06, FR-07, FR-08; downstream tasks R2-018 and R2-019 depend on this</rigor-reason>
    <dependencies>[003, 006]</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create a new class `PlaybookDispatcher` in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/`
    (factory-instantiated, NOT DI-registered) that performs two-stage playbook intent matching.

    **Stage 1 — Vector Similarity Search**:
    - Generate an embedding for the user's message text using Azure OpenAI `text-embedding-3-large`
    - Query the `playbook-embeddings` AI Search index (created in Task R2-003) using hybrid search
    - Pre-filter by `recordType` matching `ChatHostContext.RecordType` (reduces candidate set)
    - Return top 5 candidates by combined RRF score (or vector-only if no keyword match)
    - Timeout: 1.5 seconds maximum for the vector search stage

    **Stage 2 — LLM Refinement + Parameter Extraction**:
    - If Stage 1 returns 0 candidates: return `DispatchResult.NoMatch`
    - If Stage 1 returns exactly 1 candidate with score &gt;= 0.85: skip Stage 2, return match directly
    - Otherwise: send a compact prompt to the execution IChatClient asking it to:
      a. Select the best matching playbook from the candidates list (or "none")
      b. Extract any parameter values mentioned in the user message (e.g., recipient name, date)
      c. Return as structured JSON: `{ "playbookId": "...", "confidence": 0.0-1.0, "parameters": {} }`
    - Timeout: 0.5 seconds for Stage 2 (fast LLM call with small prompt)
    - Total NFR-04 budget: 2 seconds for both stages combined

    **Output**:
    ```csharp
    public record DispatchResult(
        bool Matched,
        string? PlaybookId,
        double ConfidenceScore,
        Dictionary&lt;string, string&gt; ExtractedParameters,
        string OutputType,         // text | dialog | navigation | download | insert
        bool RequiresConfirmation);
    ```

    **Class design**:
    ```csharp
    public class PlaybookDispatcher
    {
        public PlaybookDispatcher(SemanticSearchService searchService, IChatClient executionClient,
            ILogger&lt;PlaybookDispatcher&gt; logger) { ... }

        public Task&lt;DispatchResult&gt; DispatchAsync(string userMessage, ChatHostContext context,
            CancellationToken cancellationToken = default);
    }
    ```

    The `PlaybookDispatcher` is called by `SprkChatAgent` when user messages should be evaluated for
    playbook intent before generating a standard chat response.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer with Azure AI and Minimal API expertise</role>

  <goal>
    `PlaybookDispatcher` exists in `Services/Ai/Chat/`, is factory-instantiated, performs two-stage
    matching within 2 seconds (NFR-04), and returns a `DispatchResult` with playbook ID, confidence,
    extracted parameters, output type, and confirmation requirement. "Send analysis by email to John"
    matches the email playbook with `{"recipient": "John"}` extracted (FR-06).
  </goal>

