  <context>
    <background>
      The PlaybookDispatcher is the centerpiece of SprkChat R2's "copilot-quality" intent recognition.
      When a user types "send this analysis by email to the client" in SprkChat, the dispatcher:
      1. Embeds the message and searches the `playbook-embeddings` index for email-related playbooks
      2. If multiple candidates (email follow-up, email summary, email notification), asks the LLM
         to select the best match given the full user message
      3. Extracts "client" as the `recipient` parameter
      4. Returns the matched email playbook with `requiresConfirmation: true` (from JPS)
      5. Task R2-018 (PlaybookOutputHandler) then opens the email composer Code Page pre-populated

      The two-stage approach is essential for both accuracy and performance: vector search handles
      the semantic matching quickly, while LLM refinement handles ambiguous multi-candidate cases
      with parameter extraction. Single high-confidence matches skip Stage 2 to stay within NFR-04.

      `CompoundIntentDetector` (existing) handles a different use case — it detects whether the
      AI's own plan-preview response requires confirmation before execution. `PlaybookDispatcher`
      handles user natural language → playbook intent recognition. They are complementary.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      Depends on Task R2-003 (playbook-embeddings AI Search index must exist) and R2-006 (Phase 1
      deployment). Safe to run in parallel with Group A tasks (R2-010 through R2-014). Tasks R2-018
      and R2-019 depend on this. Task R2-016 (embedding pipeline) is an independent sibling in Group B.
      Own files: `Services/Ai/Chat/PlaybookDispatcher.cs`, `Models/Ai/Chat/DispatchResult.cs`.
    </dependencies>
  </context>

